==English==
=== Etymology ===
{{L.}} ''[[cōnscriptus]]'', [[past participle]] of ''[[cōnscrībere]]''

=== Pronunciation ===
*(''noun, adjective''):
**(''[[RP]]''): kŏn'skrĭpt, /ˈkɒnskrɪpt/, /<tt>"kQnskrIpt</tt>/
**(''US''): kän'skrĭpt, /ˈkɑnskrIpt/, /<tt>"kAnskrIpt</tt>/
*(''verb''): kənskrĭpt', /kənˈskrɪpt/, /<tt>k@n"skrIpt</tt>/

=== Noun ===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#one who is [[compulsorily]] [[enrol]]led, often into a [[military]] service; a [[draftee]]
#:''The soldier was a conscript.''

